e]] pioneer\n|<ref name=\"uchicago\">{{cite web|url=http://magazine.uchicago.edu/9604/9604BOBDeaths.html|title=Deaths, University of Chicago Magazine, April 96|website=magazine.uchicago.edu|accessdate=April 2, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Albert Turner Bharucha-Reid|Bharucha-Reid, Albert T.]]\n| 1927\u20131985\n| Mathematician, statistician\n| [[Probability theory]] and [[Markov chain]] theorist\n|<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">Williams, Scott W. (2008). [http://www.math.buffalo.edu/mad/PEEPS/bharucha-reid_a_t.html \"Mathematicians of the African Diaspora: Albert Turner Bharucha-Reid\"]. The Mathematics Department of the State University of New York at Buffalo. Retrieved November 25, 2012.</ref>\n|-\n| [[Keith Black (surgeon)|Black, Keith]]\n| 1957\u2013\n| [[Neurosurgeon]]\n| [[Brain tumor]] surgery and research\n|<ref name=\"book\">{{cite book| author = Keith Black| author2 = Arnold Mann| title = Brain Surgeon: A Doctor's Inspiring Encounters with Mortality and Miracles| date = March 25, 2009| publisher = Grand Central Life & Style| isbn = 978-0-446-58109-7| url = https://archive.org/details/brainsurgeondoct00blac}}</ref><ref name=\"TIME97\">Michael D. Lemonick, [http://www.time.com/time/reports/heroes/tumor.html \"The Tumor War\"], ''Time'', ''Heroes of Medicine'' special edition, Fall 1997 (retrieved May 15, 2009).</ref>\n|-\n| [[David Blackwell|Blackwell, David]]\n| 1919\u20132010\n| Mathematician, statistician\n| First proposed the [[Blackwell channel]] model used in [[coding theory]] and [[information theory]]; one of the [[eponym]]s of the [[Rao\u2013Blackwell theorem]], which is a process that significantly improves crude statistical [[estimator]]s\n|<ref name=\"UIAA\">{{cite news\n  | last =Cattau  | first =Daniel\n  | title =David Blackwell 'Superstar'  | work =Illinois Alumni  | pages =32\u201334\n  | publisher =University of Illinois Alumni Association\n  | date =July 2009  }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Henry Blair (inventor)|Blair, Henry]]\n| 1807\u20131860\n| Inventor\n| 