ut.com/od/bstartinventors/a/Otis_Boykin.htm Mary Bellis, \"Otis Boykin\"], About.com Guide.</ref><ref name=\"DallasMorningStar-1982.03.18\">\"Inventor of Heart Stimulator Honored at Memorial Service.\" ''Dallas Morning News'', March 18, 1982, p.&nbsp;88.</ref>\n|-\n| [[St. Elmo Brady|Brady, St. Elmo]]\n| 1884\u20131966\n| [[Chemist]]\n| Published three scholarly abstracts in ''Science''; collaborated on a paper published in the ''Journal of Industrial and Engineering Chemistry''\n|<ref>[http://chemistry.uiuc.edu/bios/brady.html University of Illinois biography] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060903230903/http://www.chemistry.uiuc.edu/bios/brady.html |date=September 3, 2006 }}, University of Illinois.</ref>\n|-\n| [[Herman Branson|Branson, Herman]]\n| 1914\u20131995\n| [[Physicist]], educator\n| Protein structure research\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pnas.org/misc/classics1.shtml|title=PNAS Classics \u2013 Protein Structure|website=pnas.org|accessdate=April 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Einseberg | first1 = David | year = 2003 | title = The discovery of the alpha-helix and beta-sheet, the principal structural features of proteins | journal = PNAS | volume = 100 | issue = 20| pages = 11207\u201311210 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.2034522100 | pmid=12966187 | pmc=208735}}</ref>\n|-\n| Brooks, Charles\n| 1865\u2013 ?\n| Inventor {{citation needed|date=April 2013}}\n| [[Street sweeper]] truck and a type of paper punch\n|<ref>{{cite patent|title=Street Sweeper |url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US558719A/en |country=US |number=558719A |issue-date=1896-04-21 |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite patent |title=Punch |url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US507672A/en |country=US |number=507672A |issue-date=1893-10-31 |access-date=February 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Henry Brown\n| 1832\u2013 ?\n| Inventor\n| Invented [[fire safe]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackinventor.com/pages/henrybrown|title=Henry Brown|publisher=blackinventor.com|accessdate=February 6, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930204933/http://www.blackinventor.com/pages/henrybrown|archive-date=September 30, 2011|url-status=dead}}{{cite web|url=http://www.blackinventor.com/pages/henrybrown|title=Henry Brown|publisher=blackinventor.com|accessdate=February 6, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930204933/http://www.blackinventor.com/pages/henrybrown|archive-date=September 30, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Oscar E.Brown|Brown, Oscar E.]]\n|18xx\u2013 ?\n|Inventor\n|Received a patent for an improved [[horseshoe]]<ref>{{Cite web| title = The History of Horseshoes| work = Inventors \u2013 About.com| accessdate = February 26, 2015| url = http://inventors.about.com/library/inventors/blhorseshoe.htm}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|[[Marie Van Brittan Brown|Brown, Marie Van Brittan]] \n|1922\u20131999\n|Inventor\n|Invented the home security system\n|<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/smart-living/11-african-american-inventors-who-changed-the-world/ss-BBIMZ3w|title=11 African American Inventors Who Changed the World|publisher=MSN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810174456/https://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/smart-living/11-african-american-inventors-who-changed-the-world/ss-BBIMZ3w|archive-date=August 10, 2018|url-status=|access-date=April 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Burr, John Albert\n| 18xx\u2013 ?\n| Inventor\n| [[Rotary-blade lawn mower]] patent\n|<ref>{{cite web|last=Bellis|first=Mary|title=John Albert Burr|url=http://inventors.about.com/library/inventors/bl_John_Albert_Burr.htm|work=About.com|accessdate=July 22, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|Cannon, Thomas C.\n|1943\u2013\n|Inventor\n|Led a group of engineers who developed the Tactical Optical Fiber Connector (TOFC), the first fiber optic connector deployed under battlefield conditions, and the ST Connector that helped make fiber optic communications affordable.\n|\n|-\n| [[William Warrick Cardozo|Cardozo, William Warrick]]\n| 1905\u20131962\n| [[Pediatrician]]\n| [[Sickle cell anemia]] studies; in October 1937 he published \"Immunologic Studies in Sickle Cell Anemia\" in the [[Archives of Internal Medicine]]; many of the findings are still valid today\n|\n|-\n| [[Ben Carson|Carson, Ben]]\n| 1951\u2013\n| [[Pediatrics|Pediatric]] [[neurosurgeon]]\n| [[Pediatrics|Pediatric]] [[Neurosurgeon|neurosurgery]] at [[Johns Hopkins University]]; first surgeon to successfully separate [[craniopagus twins]]\n|<ref name=\"faqs\">{{cite web|url=http://www.faqs.org/health/bios/63/Benjamin-S-Carson.html |title=Benjamin S. Carson Biography (1951\u2013)|website=faqs.org|accessdate=April 2, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[George Robert Carruthers|Carruthers, George]]\n|1939\u2013\n|[[Astrophysics|Astrophysicist]]\n|Invented ultraviolet camera/spectograph, which was used by NASA when it launched Apollo 16 in 1972\n|<ref name=\":0\" />\n|-\n| [[George Washington Carver|Carver, George Washington]]\n| 1865\u20131943\n| [[Botanical]] researcher\n| Discovered hundreds of uses for previously useless vegetables and fruits, principally the [[George Washington Carver#Reputed inventions|peanut]]\n|<ref name=\"time_article1\">{{cite news\n|title=Black Leonardo Book\n|date=November 24, 1941\n|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]\n|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,801330,00.html\n|accessdate=August 10, 2008\n}}</ref><ref>Harlan, Volume 5, p. 481</ref><ref name=\"Special_History_Study\">[http://www.nps.gov/applications/parks/gwca/ppdocuments/Special%20History%20Study.pdf Special History Study] from the [[National Park Service]] website</ref><ref>[http://www.lib.iastate.edu/spcl/gwc/friends/friends8.html The legacy of George Washington Carver-Friends & Colleagues (Henry Wallace)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415211140/http://www.lib.iastate.edu/spcl/gwc/friends/friends8.html |date=April 15, 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n | [[Charles W. Chappelle]]\n |  1872\u20131941\n |  Electrician, construction, international 